The paper deals with image denoising using machine learning techniques, specifically multi layer perceptrons (MLP). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the training trade-offs and inner mechanisms of MLPs, which are topics covered in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the adaptation of the approach to different types of noise, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
